  33 def _safe_shape_div(x, y):
  34   """Divides `x / y` assuming `x, y >= 0`, treating `0 / 0 = 0`."""
  35   return x // math_ops.maximum(y, 1)

  38 @ops.RegisterGradient("ArgMax")
  39 def _ArgMaxGrad(op, grad):
  40   del op, grad
  41   return [None, None]

  50 @ops.RegisterGradient("Sum")
  51 def _SumGrad(op, grad):
  52   """Gradient for Sum."""
  53   # Fast path for when reducing to a scalar and ndims is known: adds only
  54   # Reshape and Tile ops (and possibly a Shape).
  55   input_0_shape = op.inputs[0]._shape_tuple()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
  56   if input_0_shape is not None:
  57     axes = tensor_util.constant_value(op.inputs[1])
  58     if axes is not None:
  59       rank = len(input_0_shape)
  60       if np.array_equal(axes, np.arange(rank)):  # Reduce all dims.
  61         if context.executing_eagerly():
  62           ctx = context.context()
  63           new_shape = ctx.ones_rank_cache().get(rank)
  64           if new_shape is None:
  65             new_shape = constant_op.constant([1] * rank, dtype=dtypes.int32)
  66             ctx.ones_rank_cache().put(rank, new_shape)
  67         else:
  68           new_shape = [1] * rank
  69         grad = array_ops.reshape(grad, new_shape)
  70         # If shape is not fully defined (but rank is), we use Shape.
  71         if None not in input_0_shape:
  72           input_shape = constant_op.constant(input_0_shape, dtype=dtypes.int32)
  73         else:
  74           input_shape = array_ops.shape(op.inputs[0])
  75         return [array_ops.tile(grad, input_shape), None]
  76 
  77   input_shape = array_ops.shape(op.inputs[0])
  78   # TODO(apassos) remove this once device placement for eager ops makes more
  79   # sense.
  80   with ops.colocate_with(input_shape):
  81     output_shape_kept_dims = math_ops.reduced_shape(input_shape, op.inputs[1])
  82     tile_scaling = _safe_shape_div(input_shape, output_shape_kept_dims)
  83   grad = array_ops.reshape(grad, output_shape_kept_dims)
  84   return [array_ops.tile(grad, tile_scaling), None]
  85 
  86 
  87 def _MinOrMaxGrad(op, grad):
  88   """Gradient for Min or Max. Amazingly it's precisely the same code."""
  89   input_shape = array_ops.shape(op.inputs[0])
  90   output_shape_kept_dims = math_ops.reduced_shape(input_shape, op.inputs[1])
  91   y = op.outputs[0]
  92   y = array_ops.reshape(y, output_shape_kept_dims)
  93   grad = array_ops.reshape(grad, output_shape_kept_dims)
  94 
  95   # Compute the number of selected (maximum or minimum) elements in each
  96   # reduction dimension. If there are multiple minimum or maximum elements
  97   # then the gradient will be divided between them.
  98   indicators = math_ops.cast(math_ops.equal(y, op.inputs[0]), grad.dtype)
  99   num_selected = array_ops.reshape(
 100       math_ops.reduce_sum(indicators, op.inputs[1]), output_shape_kept_dims)
 101 
 102   return [math_ops.div(indicators, num_selected) * grad, None]
 103

 105 @ops.RegisterGradient("Max")
 106 def _MaxGrad(op, grad):

 108   return _MinOrMaxGrad(op, grad)

 112 def _MinGrad(op, grad):
 113   return _MinOrMaxGrad(op, grad)

 116 @ops.RegisterGradient("Mean")
 117 def _MeanGrad(op, grad):
 118   """Gradient for Mean."""
 119   sum_grad = _SumGrad(op, grad)[0]
 120   input_shape = op.inputs[0]._shape_tuple()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 121   output_shape = op.outputs[0]._shape_tuple()  # pylint: disable=protected-access
 122   if (input_shape is not None and output_shape is not None and
 123       None not in input_shape and None not in output_shape):
 124     input_size = np.prod(input_shape)
 125     output_size = np.prod(output_shape)
 126     factor = input_size // max(output_size, 1)
 127     factor = constant_op.constant(factor, dtype=sum_grad.dtype)
 128   else:
 129     input_shape = array_ops.shape(op.inputs[0])
 130     output_shape = array_ops.shape(op.outputs[0])
 131     factor = _safe_shape_div(
 132         math_ops.reduce_prod(input_shape), math_ops.reduce_prod(output_shape))
 133   return math_ops.truediv(sum_grad, math_ops.cast(factor, sum_grad.dtype)), None
 134

 136 @ops.RegisterGradient("Prod")
 137 def _ProdGrad(op, grad):
 138   """Gradient for Prod."""
 139   # The gradient can be expressed by dividing the product by each entry of the
 140   # input tensor, but this approach can't deal with zeros in the input.
 141   # Here, we avoid this problem by composing the output as a product of two
 142   # cumprod operations.
 143 
 144   input_shape = array_ops.shape(op.inputs[0])
 145   # Reshape reduction indices for the case where the parameter is a scalar
 146   reduction_indices = array_ops.reshape(op.inputs[1], [-1])
 147 
 148   # Expand grad to full input shape
 149   output_shape_kept_dims = math_ops.reduced_shape(input_shape, op.inputs[1])
 150   tile_scaling = _safe_shape_div(input_shape, output_shape_kept_dims)
 151   grad = array_ops.reshape(grad, output_shape_kept_dims)
 152   grad = array_ops.tile(grad, tile_scaling)
 153 
 154   # Pack all reduced dimensions into a single one, so we can perform the
 155   # cumprod ops. If the reduction dims list is empty, it defaults to float32,
 156   # so we need to cast here.  We put all the shape-related ops on CPU to avoid
 157   # copying back and forth, and since listdiff is CPU only.
 158   with ops.device("/cpu:0"):
 159     rank = array_ops.rank(op.inputs[0])
 160     reduction_indices = (reduction_indices + rank) % rank
 161     reduced = math_ops.cast(reduction_indices, dtypes.int32)
 162     idx = math_ops.range(0, rank)
 163     other, _ = array_ops.setdiff1d(idx, reduced)
 164     perm = array_ops.concat([reduced, other], 0)
 165     reduced_num = math_ops.reduce_prod(array_ops.gather(input_shape, reduced))
 166     other_num = math_ops.reduce_prod(array_ops.gather(input_shape, other))
 167   permuted = array_ops.transpose(op.inputs[0], perm)
 168   permuted_shape = array_ops.shape(permuted)
 169   reshaped = array_ops.reshape(permuted, (reduced_num, other_num))
 170 
 171   # Calculate product, leaving out the current entry
 172   left = math_ops.cumprod(reshaped, axis=0, exclusive=True)
 173   right = math_ops.cumprod(reshaped, axis=0, exclusive=True, reverse=True)
 174   # For complex inputs, the gradient is in the conjugate direction.
 175   y = array_ops.reshape(math_ops.conj(left) * math_ops.conj(right),
 176                         permuted_shape)
 177 
 178   # Invert the transpose and reshape operations.
 179   # Make sure to set the statically known shape information through a reshape.
 180   out = grad * array_ops.transpose(y, array_ops.invert_permutation(perm))
 181   return array_ops.reshape(out, input_shape), None
 182

 184 @ops.RegisterGradient("SegmentSum")
 185 def _SegmentSumGrad(op, grad):
 186   """Gradient for SegmentSum."""
 187   return array_ops.gather(grad, op.inputs[1]), None

 190 @ops.RegisterGradient("SegmentMean")
 191 def _SegmentMeanGrad(op, grad):
 192   """Gradient for SegmentMean."""
 193   input_rank = array_ops.rank(op.inputs[0])
 194   ones_shape = array_ops.concat([
 195       array_ops.shape(op.inputs[1]),
 196       array_ops.fill(array_ops.expand_dims(input_rank - 1, 0), 1)
 197   ], 0)
 198   ones = array_ops.fill(ones_shape, constant_op.constant(1, dtype=grad.dtype))
 199   scaled_grad = math_ops.div(grad, math_ops.segment_sum(ones, op.inputs[1]))
 200   return array_ops.gather(scaled_grad, op.inputs[1]), None

 208       array_ops.gather(grad, op.inputs[2]), op.inputs[1], input_rows), None,
 209           None)

 253 def _SegmentMinOrMaxGrad(op, grad):
 254   """ Gradient for SegmentMin and SegmentMax. """
 255   zeros = array_ops.zeros_like(op.inputs[0], dtype=op.inputs[0].dtype)
 256   # Get the number of selected (minimum or maximum) elements in each segment.
 257   gathered_outputs = array_ops.gather(op.outputs[0], op.inputs[1])
 258   is_selected = math_ops.equal(op.inputs[0], gathered_outputs)
 259   num_selected = math_ops.segment_sum(math_ops.cast(is_selected, grad.dtype),
 260                                       op.inputs[1])
 261   # Compute the gradient for each segment. The gradient for the ith segment is
 262   # divided evenly among the selected elements in that segment.
 263   weighted_grads = math_ops.div(grad, num_selected)
 264   gathered_grads = array_ops.gather(weighted_grads, op.inputs[1])
 265   return array_ops.where(is_selected, gathered_grads, zeros), None
 266 
 267

 270   """Gradient for SegmentMin."""
 271   return _SegmentMinOrMaxGrad(op, grad)

 275 def _SegmentMaxGrad(op, grad):
 276   """Gradient for SegmentMax."""
 277   return _SegmentMinOrMaxGrad(op, grad)

 280 def _GatherDropNegatives(params, ids, zero_clipped_indices=None,
 281                          is_positive=None):
 282   """ Helper function for unsorted segment ops. Gathers params for
 283       positive segment ids and gathers 0 for inputs with negative segment id.
 284       Also returns the clipped indices and a boolean mask with the same shape
 285       as ids where a positive id is masked as true. With this, the latter two
 286       can be passed as arguments to this function to reuse them.
 287   """
 288   if zero_clipped_indices is None:
 289     zero_clipped_indices = math_ops.maximum(ids, array_ops.zeros_like(ids))
 290   gathered = array_ops.gather(params, zero_clipped_indices)
 291   if is_positive is None:
 292     is_positive = math_ops.greater_equal(ids, 0)
 293     # tf.where(condition, x, y) requires condition to have the same shape as x
 294     # and y.
 295     # todo(philjd): remove this if tf.where supports broadcasting (#9284)
 296     for _ in range(gathered.shape.ndims - is_positive.shape.ndims):
 297       is_positive = array_ops.expand_dims(is_positive, -1)
 298     is_positive = (is_positive &
 299                    array_ops.ones_like(gathered, dtype=dtypes.bool))
 300   # replace gathered params of negative indices with 0
 301   zero_slice = array_ops.zeros_like(gathered)
 302   return (array_ops.where(is_positive, gathered, zero_slice),
 303           zero_clipped_indices, is_positive)
 304 
 305 
 306 def _UnsortedSegmentMinOrMaxGrad(op, grad):
 307   """ Gradient for UnsortedSegmentMin and UnsortedSegmentMax. """
 308   # Get the number of selected (minimum or maximum) elements in each segment.
 309   gathered_outputs, zero_clipped_indices, is_positive = \
 310       _GatherDropNegatives(op.outputs[0], op.inputs[1])
 311   is_selected = math_ops.equal(op.inputs[0], gathered_outputs)
 312   is_selected = math_ops.logical_and(is_selected, is_positive)
 313   num_selected = math_ops.unsorted_segment_sum(
 314       math_ops.cast(is_selected, grad.dtype), op.inputs[1], op.inputs[2])
 315   # Compute the gradient for each segment. The gradient for the ith segment is
 316   # divided evenly among the selected elements in that segment.
 317   weighted_grads = math_ops.div(grad, num_selected)
 318   gathered_grads, _, _ = _GatherDropNegatives(weighted_grads, None,
 319                                               zero_clipped_indices,
 320                                               is_positive)
 321   zeros = array_ops.zeros_like(gathered_grads)
 322   return array_ops.where(is_selected, gathered_grads, zeros), None, None
 323 
 324

 343 @ops.RegisterGradient("UnsortedSegmentProd")
 344 def _UnsortedSegmentProdGrad(op, grad):
 345   """ Gradient for UnsortedSegmentProd.
 346   The gradient can be expressed for each segment by dividing the segment's
 347   product by each element of the segment input tensor, but this approach can't
 348   deal with zeros in the input.
 349   Unlike reduce_prod we can't use cumsum here as individual segments may have
 350   a different number of elements. Therefore we consider three cases:
 351   1) A segment input contains no zeros and we can safely divide by the input
 352      tensor.
 353   2) A segment contains exactly one zero. Then the gradient of each input of
 354      the segment is zero except for the 0-input, there the gradient is
 355      the product of the remaining segment entries.
 356   3) A segment contains at least two zeros. The gradient is zero for all
 357      segment inputs.
 358   """
 359   # Note that unsorted_segment_sum will filter out the negative indices,
 360   # so we don't need to do a logical_and with is_positive here
 361   is_zero = math_ops.equal(op.inputs[0], 0)
 362   num_zeros = gen_math_ops.unsorted_segment_sum(
 363       math_ops.cast(is_zero, dtype=dtypes.int32), op.inputs[1], op.inputs[2])
 364   # handle case 3 and set the gradient to 0 for segments with more than one
 365   # 0 as input
 366   grad = array_ops.where(math_ops.greater(num_zeros, 1),
 367                          array_ops.zeros_like(grad), grad)
 368   # replace all zeros with ones and compute the unsorted_segment_prod
 369   non_zero_data = array_ops.where(is_zero, array_ops.ones_like(op.inputs[0]),
 370                                   op.inputs[0])
 371   non_zero_prod = gen_math_ops.unsorted_segment_prod(
 372       non_zero_data, op.inputs[1], op.inputs[2])
 373   # clip the indices for gather to be positive
 374   zero_clipped_indices = math_ops.maximum(op.inputs[1],
 375                                           array_ops.zeros_like(op.inputs[1]))
 376   gathered_prod = array_ops.gather(op.outputs[0], zero_clipped_indices)
 377   gathered_non_zero_prod = array_ops.gather(non_zero_prod,
 378                                             zero_clipped_indices)
 379   prod_divided_by_el = gathered_prod / op.inputs[0]  # May contain nan/inf.
 380   # Now fetch the individual results for segments containing 0 and those that
 381   # don't. is_zero will also fetch results for entries with negative index
 382   # but the following gather_drop_negatives sets the corresponding entry in
 383   # grad to 0 for these
 384   partial_derivative = array_ops.where(is_zero, gathered_non_zero_prod,
 385                                        prod_divided_by_el)
 386   gathered_grad = _GatherDropNegatives(grad, op.inputs[1],
 387                                        zero_clipped_indices)[0]
 388   return gathered_grad * partial_derivative, None, None
 389

 391 @ops.RegisterGradient("Abs")
 392 def _AbsGrad(op, grad):
 393   x = op.inputs[0]
 394   return grad * math_ops.sign(x)

 397 @ops.RegisterGradient("Neg")
 398 def _NegGrad(_, grad):
 399   """Returns -grad."""
 400   return -grad

 403 @ops.RegisterGradient("Inv")
 404 def _InvGrad(op, grad):
 405   """Returns -grad * (1 / x^2)."""
 406   y = op.outputs[0]  # y = 1 / x
 407   return gen_math_ops.reciprocal_grad(y, grad)
 408

 410 @ops.RegisterGradient("Reciprocal")
 411 def _ReciprocalGrad(op, grad):
 412   """Returns -grad * (1 / x^2)."""
 413   y = op.outputs[0]  # y = 1 / x
 414   return gen_math_ops.reciprocal_grad(y, grad)
 415

 417 @ops.RegisterGradient("InvGrad")
 418 def _InvGradGrad(op, grad):
 419   b = op.inputs[1]
 420   # op.output[0]: y = -b * conj(a)^2
 421   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 422     ca = math_ops.conj(op.inputs[0])
 423     cg = math_ops.conj(grad)
 424     return cg * -2.0 * b * ca, gen_math_ops.reciprocal_grad(ca, grad)
 425 
 426 
 427 @ops.RegisterGradient("ReciprocalGrad")
 428 def _ReciprocalGradGrad(op, grad):
 429   b = op.inputs[1]
 430   # op.output[0]: y = -b * conj(a)^2
 431   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 432     ca = math_ops.conj(op.inputs[0])
 433     cg = math_ops.conj(grad)
 434     return cg * -2.0 * b * ca, gen_math_ops.reciprocal_grad(ca, grad)
 435

 437 @ops.RegisterGradient("Square")
 438 def _SquareGrad(op, grad):
 439   x = op.inputs[0]
 440   # Added control dependencies to prevent 2*x from being computed too early.
 441   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 442     x = math_ops.conj(x)
 443     y = constant_op.constant(2.0, dtype=x.dtype)
 444     return math_ops.multiply(grad, math_ops.multiply(x, y))
 445 
 446 
 447 @ops.RegisterGradient("Sqrt")
 448 def _SqrtGrad(op, grad):
 449   y = op.outputs[0]  # y = x^(1/2)
 450   return gen_math_ops.sqrt_grad(y, grad)
 451 
 452 
 453 @ops.RegisterGradient("SqrtGrad")
 454 def _SqrtGradGrad(op, grad):
 455   a = op.inputs[0]
 456   y = op.outputs[0]  # y = 0.5 * b / conj(a)
 457   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 458     ga = grad / a
 459     return -math_ops.conj(ga) * y, 0.5 * ga
 460

 462 @ops.RegisterGradient("Rsqrt")
 463 def _RsqrtGrad(op, grad):
 464   """Returns -0.5 * grad * conj(y)^3."""
 465   y = op.outputs[0]  # y = x^(-1/2)
 466   return gen_math_ops.rsqrt_grad(y, grad)

 469 @ops.RegisterGradient("RsqrtGrad")
 470 def _RsqrtGradGrad(op, grad):
 471   """Returns backprop gradient for f(a,b) = -0.5 * b * conj(a)^3."""
 472   a = op.inputs[0]  # a = x^{-1/2}
 473   b = op.inputs[1]  # backprop gradient for a
 474   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 475     ca = math_ops.conj(a)
 476     cg = math_ops.conj(grad)
 477     grad_a = -1.5 * cg * b * math_ops.square(ca)
 478     grad_b = gen_math_ops.rsqrt_grad(ca, grad)
 479     return grad_a, grad_b
 480

 519 @ops.RegisterGradient("Xlogy")
 520 def _XLogyGrad(op, grad):
 521   """Returns gradient of xlogy(x, y) with respect to x and y."""
 522   x = op.inputs[0]
 523   y = op.inputs[1]
 524   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 525   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
 526   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
 527   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 528     not_zero_x = math_ops.cast(
 529         math_ops.not_equal(x, math_ops.cast(0., dtype=x.dtype)), dtype=x.dtype)
 530     partial_x = gen_math_ops.xlogy(not_zero_x, y)
 531     partial_y = gen_math_ops.xdivy(x, y)
 532     return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_x * grad, rx), sx),
 533             array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_y * grad, ry), sy))
 534

 536 @ops.RegisterGradient("Xdivy")

 538   """Returns gradient of xdivy(x, y) with respect to x and y."""
 539   x = op.inputs[0]
 540   y = op.inputs[1]
 541   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 542   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
 543   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
 544   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 545     not_zero_x = math_ops.cast(
 546         math_ops.not_equal(x, math_ops.cast(0., dtype=x.dtype)), dtype=x.dtype)
 547     partial_x = gen_math_ops.xdivy(not_zero_x, y)
 548     partial_y = gen_math_ops.xdivy(math_ops.negative(x), y**2)
 549     return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_x * grad, rx), sx),
 550             array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_y * grad, ry), sy))

 657 @ops.RegisterGradient("BesselI0e")
 658 def _BesselI0eGrad(op, grad):
 659   """Compute gradient of bessel_i0e(x) with respect to its argument."""
 660   x = op.inputs[0]
 661   y = op.outputs[0]
 662   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 663     return grad * (math_ops.bessel_i1e(x) - math_ops.sign(x) * y)
 664 
 665 
 666 @ops.RegisterGradient("BesselI1e")
 667 def _BesselI1eGrad(op, grad):
 668   """Compute gradient of bessel_i1e(x) with respect to its argument."""
 669   x = op.inputs[0]
 670   y = op.outputs[0]
 671   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 672     # For x = 0, the correct gradient is 0.5.
 673     # However, the main branch gives NaN because of the division by x, so
 674     # we impute the gradient manually.
 675     # An alternative solution is to express the gradient via bessel_i0e and
 676     # bessel_i2e, but the latter is not yet implemented in Eigen.
 677     eps = np.finfo(x.dtype.as_numpy_dtype).eps
 678     zeros = array_ops.zeros_like(x)
 679     x_is_not_tiny = math_ops.abs(x) > eps
 680     safe_x = array_ops.where(x_is_not_tiny, x, eps + zeros)
 681     dy_dx = math_ops.bessel_i0e(safe_x) - y * (
 682         math_ops.sign(safe_x) + math_ops.reciprocal(safe_x))
 683     return grad * array_ops.where(x_is_not_tiny, dy_dx, 0.5 + zeros)
 684

 686 @ops.RegisterGradient("Igamma")
 687 def _IgammaGrad(op, grad):
 688   """Returns gradient of igamma(a, x) with respect to a and x."""
 689   a = op.inputs[0]
 690   x = op.inputs[1]
 691   sa = array_ops.shape(a)
 692   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 693   ra, rx = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sa, sx)
 694 
 695   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 696     partial_a = gen_math_ops.igamma_grad_a(a, x)
 697     # Perform operations in log space before summing, because Gamma(a)
 698     # and Gamma'(a) can grow large.
 699     partial_x = math_ops.exp(-x + (a - 1) * math_ops.log(x)
 700                              - math_ops.lgamma(a))
 701     return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_a * grad, ra), sa),
 702             array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_x * grad, rx), sx))
 703

 705 @ops.RegisterGradient("Igammac")
 706 def _IgammacGrad(op, grad):
 707   """Returns gradient of igammac(a, x) = 1 - igamma(a, x) w.r.t. a and x."""
 708   igamma_grad_a, igamma_grad_x = _IgammaGrad(op, grad)
 709   return (-igamma_grad_a, -igamma_grad_x)

 712 @ops.RegisterGradient("Betainc")
 713 def _BetaincGrad(op, grad):
 714   """Returns gradient of betainc(a, b, x) with respect to x."""
 715   # TODO(ebrevdo): Perhaps add the derivative w.r.t. a, b
 716   a, b, x = op.inputs
 717 
 718   # two cases: x is a scalar and a/b are same-shaped tensors, or vice
 719   # versa; so its sufficient to check against shape(a).
 720   sa = array_ops.shape(a)
 721   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 722   _, rx = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sa, sx)
 723 
 724   # Perform operations in log space before summing, because terms
 725   # can grow large.
 726   log_beta = (
 727       gen_math_ops.lgamma(a) + gen_math_ops.lgamma(b) -
 728       gen_math_ops.lgamma(a + b))
 729   partial_x = math_ops.exp((b - 1) * math_ops.log(1 - x) +
 730                            (a - 1) * math_ops.log(x) - log_beta)
 731 
 732   # TODO(b/36815900): Mark None return values as NotImplemented
 733   return (
 734       None,  # da
 735       None,  # db
 736       array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_x * grad, rx), sx))
 737

 739 @ops.RegisterGradient("Zeta")
 740 def _ZetaGrad(op, grad):
 741   """Returns gradient of zeta(x, q) with respect to x and q."""
 742   # TODO(tillahoffmann): Add derivative with respect to x
 743   x = op.inputs[0]
 744   q = op.inputs[1]
 745   # Broadcast gradients
 746   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 747   sq = array_ops.shape(q)
 748   unused_rx, rq = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sq)
 749   # Evaluate gradient
 750   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
 751     x = math_ops.conj(x)
 752     q = math_ops.conj(q)
 753     partial_q = -x * math_ops.zeta(x + 1, q)
 754     # TODO(b/36815900): Mark None return values as NotImplemented
 755     return (None,
 756             array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(partial_q * grad, rq), sq))

 888 def _ShapesFullySpecifiedAndEqual(x, y, grad):
 889   # pylint: disable=protected-access
 890   x_shape = x._shape_tuple()
 891   y_shape = y._shape_tuple()
 892   grad_shape = grad._shape_tuple()
 893   # pylint: enable=protected-access
 894   return (x_shape == y_shape and x_shape == grad_shape and
 895           x_shape is not None and None not in x_shape)
 896 
 897 
 898 @ops.RegisterGradient("Add")
 899 def _AddGrad(op, grad):
 900   """Gradient for Add."""
 901   x = op.inputs[0]
 902   y = op.inputs[1]
 903   if (isinstance(grad, ops.Tensor) and
 904       _ShapesFullySpecifiedAndEqual(x, y, grad)):
 905     return grad, grad
 906   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 907   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
 908   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
 909   return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(grad, rx), sx),
 910           array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(grad, ry), sy))
 911 
 912 
 913 @ops.RegisterGradient("Sub")
 914 def _SubGrad(op, grad):
 915   """Gradient for Sub."""
 916   x = op.inputs[0]
 917   y = op.inputs[1]
 918   if (isinstance(grad, ops.Tensor) and
 919       _ShapesFullySpecifiedAndEqual(x, y, grad)):
 920     return grad, -grad
 921   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 922   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
 923   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
 924   return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(grad, rx), sx),
 925           array_ops.reshape(-math_ops.reduce_sum(grad, ry), sy))
 926 
 927 
 928 @ops.RegisterGradient("Mul")
 929 def _MulGrad(op, grad):
 930   """The gradient of scalar multiplication."""
 931   x = op.inputs[0]
 932   y = op.inputs[1]
 933   if (isinstance(grad, ops.Tensor) and
 934       _ShapesFullySpecifiedAndEqual(x, y, grad) and
 935       grad.dtype in (dtypes.int32, dtypes.float32)):
 936     return gen_math_ops.mul(grad, y), gen_math_ops.mul(grad, x)
 937   assert x.dtype.base_dtype == y.dtype.base_dtype, (x.dtype, " vs. ", y.dtype)
 938   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
 939   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
 940   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
 941   x = math_ops.conj(x)
 942   y = math_ops.conj(y)
 943   return (array_ops.reshape(
 944       math_ops.reduce_sum(gen_math_ops.mul(grad, y), rx), sx),
 945           array_ops.reshape(
 946               math_ops.reduce_sum(gen_math_ops.mul(x, grad), ry), sy))
 947

1027 @ops.RegisterGradient("Pow")
1028 def _PowGrad(op, grad):
1029   """Returns grad * (y*x^(y-1), z*log(x))."""
1030   x = op.inputs[0]
1031   y = op.inputs[1]
1032   z = op.outputs[0]
1033   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
1034   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
1035   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
1036   x = math_ops.conj(x)
1037   y = math_ops.conj(y)
1038   z = math_ops.conj(z)
1039   gx = array_ops.reshape(
1040       math_ops.reduce_sum(grad * y * math_ops.pow(x, y - 1), rx), sx)
1041   # Avoid false singularity at x = 0
1042   if x.dtype.is_complex:
1043     # real(x) < 0 is fine for the complex case
1044     log_x = array_ops.where(
1045         math_ops.not_equal(x, 0), math_ops.log(x), array_ops.zeros_like(x))
1046   else:
1047     # There's no sensible real value to return if x < 0, so return 0
1048     log_x = array_ops.where(x > 0, math_ops.log(x), array_ops.zeros_like(x))
1049   gy = array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(grad * z * log_x, ry), sy)
1050   return gx, gy
1051 
1052 
1053 def _MaximumMinimumGrad(op, grad, selector_op):
1054   """Factor out the code for the gradient of Maximum or Minimum."""
1055   x = op.inputs[0]
1056   y = op.inputs[1]
1057   gdtype = grad.dtype
1058   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
1059   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
1060   gradshape = array_ops.shape(grad)
1061   zeros = array_ops.zeros(gradshape, gdtype)
1062   xmask = selector_op(x, y)
1063   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
1064   xgrad = array_ops.where(xmask, grad, zeros)
1065   ygrad = array_ops.where(xmask, zeros, grad)
1066   gx = array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(xgrad, rx), sx)
1067   gy = array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(ygrad, ry), sy)
1068   return (gx, gy)
1069

1072 def _MaximumGrad(op, grad):
1073   """Returns grad*(x > y, x <= y) with type of grad."""
1074   return _MaximumMinimumGrad(op, grad, math_ops.greater_equal)

1079   """Returns grad*(x < y, x >= y) with type of grad."""
1080   return _MaximumMinimumGrad(op, grad, math_ops.less_equal)

1083 @ops.RegisterGradient("SquaredDifference")
1084 def _SquaredDifferenceGrad(op, grad):
1085   """Returns the gradient for (x-y)^2."""
1086   x = op.inputs[0]
1087   y = op.inputs[1]
1088   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
1089   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
1090   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
1091   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
1092     # The parens ensure that if grad is IndexedSlices, it'll get multiplied by
1093     # Tensor (not a number like 2.0) which causes it to convert to Tensor.
1094     x_grad = math_ops.scalar_mul(2.0, grad) * (x - y)
1095   return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(x_grad, rx), sx),
1096           -array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(x_grad, ry), sy))

1121 @ops.RegisterGradient("MatMul")
1122 def _MatMulGrad(op, grad):
1123   """Gradient for MatMul."""
1124 
1125   t_a = op.get_attr("transpose_a")
1126   t_b = op.get_attr("transpose_b")
1127   a = math_ops.conj(op.inputs[0])
1128   b = math_ops.conj(op.inputs[1])
1129   if not t_a and not t_b:
1130     grad_a = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(grad, b, transpose_b=True)
1131     grad_b = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(a, grad, transpose_a=True)
1132   elif not t_a and t_b:
1133     grad_a = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(grad, b)
1134     grad_b = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(grad, a, transpose_a=True)
1135   elif t_a and not t_b:
1136     grad_a = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(b, grad, transpose_b=True)
1137     grad_b = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(a, grad)
1138   elif t_a and t_b:
1139     grad_a = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(b, grad, transpose_a=True, transpose_b=True)
1140     grad_b = gen_math_ops.mat_mul(grad, a, transpose_a=True, transpose_b=True)
1141   return grad_a, grad_b

1144 @ops.RegisterGradient("SparseMatMul")
1145 def _SparseMatMulGrad(op, grad):
1146   """Gradient for SparseMatMul."""
1147 
1148   t_a = op.get_attr("transpose_a")
1149   t_b = op.get_attr("transpose_b")
1150   is_sparse = {
1151       op.inputs[0]: op.get_attr("a_is_sparse"),
1152       op.inputs[1]: op.get_attr("b_is_sparse"),
1153       # Use heuristic to figure out if grad might be sparse
1154       grad: not context.executing_eagerly() and (grad.op.type == "ReluGrad")
1155   }
1156 
1157   def _SparseMatMul(t1, t2, out_dtype, transpose_a=False, transpose_b=False):
1158     """Helper function to create SparseMatMul op."""
1159 
1160     assert t1 in is_sparse and t2 in is_sparse
1161     t1_sparse = is_sparse[t1]
1162     t2_sparse = is_sparse[t2]
1163     if transpose_b:
1164       t2 = array_ops.transpose(t2)
1165       transpose_b = False
1166     prod = math_ops.matmul(
1167         t1,
1168         t2,
1169         transpose_a=transpose_a,
1170         transpose_b=transpose_b,
1171         a_is_sparse=t1_sparse,
1172         b_is_sparse=t2_sparse)
1173     if prod.dtype != out_dtype:
1174       prod = math_ops.cast(prod, out_dtype)
1175     return prod
1176 
1177   dtype_a = op.inputs[0].dtype
1178   dtype_b = op.inputs[1].dtype
1179   if not t_a and not t_b:
1180     return (_SparseMatMul(grad, op.inputs[1], dtype_a, transpose_b=True),
1181             _SparseMatMul(op.inputs[0], grad, dtype_b, transpose_a=True))
1182   elif not t_a and t_b:
1183     return (_SparseMatMul(grad, op.inputs[1], dtype_a),
1184             _SparseMatMul(grad, op.inputs[0], dtype_b, transpose_a=True))
1185   elif t_a and not t_b:
1186     return (_SparseMatMul(op.inputs[1], grad, dtype_a, transpose_b=True),
1187             _SparseMatMul(op.inputs[0], grad, dtype_b))
1188   elif t_a and t_b:
1189     return (_SparseMatMul(
1190         op.inputs[1], grad, dtype_a, transpose_a=True, transpose_b=True),
1191             _SparseMatMul(
1192                 grad, op.inputs[0], dtype_b, transpose_a=True,
1193                 transpose_b=True))
1194

1217 @ops.RegisterGradient("BatchMatMul")
1218 def _BatchMatMul(op, grad):
1219   """Returns the gradient of x and y given the gradient of x * y."""
1220   x = op.inputs[0]
1221   y = op.inputs[1]
1222   adj_x = op.get_attr("adj_x")
1223   adj_y = op.get_attr("adj_y")
1224 
1225   if not adj_x:
1226     if not adj_y:
1227       grad_x = math_ops.matmul(grad, y, adjoint_a=False, adjoint_b=True)
1228       grad_y = math_ops.matmul(x, grad, adjoint_a=True, adjoint_b=False)
1229     else:
1230       grad_x = math_ops.matmul(grad, y, adjoint_a=False, adjoint_b=False)
1231       grad_y = math_ops.matmul(grad, x, adjoint_a=True, adjoint_b=False)
1232   else:
1233     if not adj_y:
1234       grad_x = math_ops.matmul(y, grad, adjoint_a=False, adjoint_b=True)
1235       grad_y = math_ops.matmul(x, grad, adjoint_a=False, adjoint_b=False)
1236     else:
1237       grad_x = math_ops.matmul(y, grad, adjoint_a=True, adjoint_b=True)
1238       grad_y = math_ops.matmul(grad, x, adjoint_a=True, adjoint_b=True)
1239 
1240   return grad_x, grad_y

1247 @ops.RegisterGradient("Complex")
1248 def _ComplexGrad(op, grad):
1249   """Returns the real and imaginary components of 'grad', respectively."""
1250   x = op.inputs[0]
1251   y = op.inputs[1]
1252   sx = array_ops.shape(x)
1253   sy = array_ops.shape(y)
1254   rx, ry = gen_array_ops.broadcast_gradient_args(sx, sy)
1255   return (array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(math_ops.real(grad), rx), sx),
1256           array_ops.reshape(math_ops.reduce_sum(math_ops.imag(grad), ry), sy))

1260 def _RealGrad(_, grad):
1261   """Returns 'grad' as the real part and set the imaginary part 0."""
1262   zero = constant_op.constant(0, dtype=grad.dtype)
1263   return math_ops.complex(grad, zero)

1273 @ops.RegisterGradient("Angle")
1274 def _AngleGrad(op, grad):
1275   """Returns -grad / (Im(x) + iRe(x))"""
1276   x = op.inputs[0]
1277   with ops.control_dependencies([grad]):
1278     re = math_ops.real(x)
1279     im = math_ops.imag(x)
1280     z = math_ops.reciprocal(math_ops.complex(im, re))
1281     zero = constant_op.constant(0, dtype=grad.dtype)
1282     complex_grad = math_ops.complex(grad, zero)
1283     return -complex_grad * z

1288   """Returns the complex conjugate of grad."""
1289   return math_ops.conj(grad)

1292 @ops.RegisterGradient("ComplexAbs")
1293 def _ComplexAbsGrad(op, grad):
1294   """Returns the gradient of ComplexAbs."""
1295   # TODO(b/27786104): The cast to complex could be removed once arithmetic
1296   # supports mixtures of complex64 and real values.
1297   return (math_ops.complex(grad, array_ops.zeros_like(grad)) * math_ops.sign(
1298       op.inputs[0]))

1301 @ops.RegisterGradient("Cast")
1302 def _CastGrad(op, grad):
1303   t = [
1304       dtypes.float16, dtypes.float32, dtypes.float64, dtypes.bfloat16,
1305       dtypes.complex64, dtypes.complex128
1306   ]
1307   src_type = op.inputs[0].dtype.base_dtype
1308   dst_type = grad.dtype.base_dtype
1309   if src_type in t and dst_type in t:
1310     return math_ops.cast(grad, src_type)
1311   else:
1312     return None

1322 @ops.RegisterGradient("Cumsum")
1323 def _CumsumGrad(op, grad):
1324   axis = op.inputs[1]
1325   exclusive = op.get_attr("exclusive")
1326   reverse = op.get_attr("reverse")
1327   return [
1328       math_ops.cumsum(grad, axis, exclusive=exclusive, reverse=not reverse),
1329       None
1330   ]

1333 @ops.RegisterGradient("Cumprod")
1334 def _CumprodGrad(op, grad):
1335   x = op.inputs[0]
1336   axis = op.inputs[1]
1337   exclusive = op.get_attr("exclusive")
1338   reverse = op.get_attr("reverse")
1339 
1340   # TODO This fails when x contains 0 and should be fixed
1341   prod = math_ops.cumprod(x, axis, exclusive=exclusive, reverse=reverse)
1342   out = math_ops.cumsum(
1343       prod * grad, axis, exclusive=exclusive, reverse=not reverse)
1344   return [out / x, None]
